# 1. 始まりの日

Ichika: Let's see... I've got my pencil case and folders...
Ichika: That should be everything.
Ichika's Mother's Voice: Ichika! You're going to be late for the opening ceremony if you keep dallying.
Ichika: Oh... Don't worry! I'll be out the door soon!
Ichika: (Starting today, I'm a second-year...)
Ichika: (But I don't really feel like one.)
???: <Good morning, Ichika.>
Ichika: Huh?
Ichika: Miku! What are you doing here at this time of day?
Miku: <I wanted to see how you were doing. You're a second-year starting today, right?>
Miku: <I became a little curious. I was hoping to see what your new class and opening ceremony are going to be like.>
Ichika: What they're like...?
Ichika: I mean... Neither is going to feel all that special. I'm not sure if there'll be anything worth seeing...
Miku: <Really? I consider it a big day since it marks the beginning of so many new things.>
Ichika: New things... Yeah, I guess you're right.
Ichika's Mother's Voice: Ichika! I'm serious! You're going to be late!
Ichika: Oh, that's my cue to head out...!
Ichika: I'll keep my phone in my pocket. You should be fine as long as you stay hidden while you watch like usual.
Ichika: Anyway, let's get going.
Miku: <Okay!>
Miku: <Wow. There's a ton of people gathered over there.>
Ichika: I'm guessing they've posted the new class rosters by the front entrance.
Miku: <I see. That explains the buzz in the air.>
???: Hey, Ichi!!!
Ichika: Morning, Saki.
Saki: Morning, Ichi! Hey, about the new class rosters...
Miku: <Good morning, Saki. You're as peppy as ever this morning.>
Saki: What?! Miku?! What are you doing here...?
Miku: <I wanted to see what you girls are like now that you're second-years, as well as the opening ceremony.>
Miku: <While staying hidden from view, of course.>
Saki: Really?! That means you also get to share in this fun and exciting moment!
Miku: <Fun and exciting?>
Saki: Yeah!
Saki: We're gonna take a look at the new rosters now!
Saki: It's so fun and exciting because we get to find out who we're going to be with this upcoming year!
Miku: <I see. Now I understand.>
Ichika: Wait, Saki, you haven't seen them yet...?
Saki: Nope! I wanted to see them as a group!
Shiho: ...which is how we ended up waiting here for what felt like forever.
Honami: Miku, good morning. I didn't realize you'd be joining us.
Miku: <Shiho! Honami!>
Ichika: Were you all waiting for me to get here? Sorry about that.
Honami: No, that's okay.
Honami: I was also hoping that we'd get to look at them together. It is always more fun that way.
Saki: Yeah! That was my point exactly!
Shiho: I didn't have a problem with looking at them alone, but Saki insisted.
Saki: What?! Shiho, that's so cold!
Shiho: Okay, relax. We're all here now, so let's go take a look before the bell rings.
Ichika: Hehe. Yes, let's.
Miku: <So many people...>
Shiho: I think we're close enough to see them now. Let's see... We're...
Ichika: Oh, there! I'm in Class A.
Honami: I'm there too...! That means...
Honami: Ichika! We're in the same class!
Ichika: *Gasp* Yeah!
Saki: Huh?! You are?! What about me...?
Saki: Nooo! I'm not in Class A!
Shiho: Saki, look over there. You're in Class B.
Saki: What? Hey, you're right...!
Saki: But I'm not with Ichi and Hona...
Shiho: No, you're not with them. Instead...
Ichika: Wait! Shiho, Saki, you're in the same class!
Saki: What?!
Shiho: Exactly. Check it out.
Saki: You're right!!!! Thank goodness, Shiho!!!!
Shiho: Whoa! Okay, try to calm down...
Honami: Hehe. I'm so glad for you, Saki.
Teacher: Everyone! If you've already found your names, please start making your way towards your classes to prevent unnecessary crowding!
Saki: Oh, okay!
Ichika: Then, shall we?
Miku: <Hehe...>
Ichika: Is something the matter, Miku?
Miku: <I was just feeling glad that I came over.>
Ichika: What...?
Miku: <You said it wouldn't feel all that special, Ichika, but I'm having a lot of fun.>
Miku: <I got to see that look of anticipation on your faces, the joy you felt when you found out you'd be in the same classes, all sorts of things.>
Miku: <Seeing you girls... It feels like...>
Miku: <Like something new is really about to start today.>
Ichika: Something new...
Ichika: Right...
Miku: <Ichika?>
Ichika: I had it in my mind that we'd just be shuffling classes and going to a new classroom...
Ichika: But “just” might not be appropriate.
Ichika: Today's a day that marks the beginning of a lot of new things.
Ichika: So...
Ichika: I'm going to start treating this day like it's special and really try to cherish it.
Miku: <Okay.>
Miku: <Try to have as much fun as you can today, Ichika!>
Ichika: I will!
Saki's Voice: Ichi! We're gonna be late!
Ichika: Oh...! Sorry, be right there!
Ichika: Anyway, Miku, I hope you'll take a good look at what happens at our school and see how we all do today.
